.TH WAYBACK 1 "2026-05-29" "0.1.9" "Wayback Machine Downloader"
.\"
.\" wayback.1 - manual page for the wayback CLI tool
.\" SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
.\"
.SH NAME
wayback \- browser-impersonated Wayback Machine asset downloader
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wayback
.B \-\-url
.I DOMAIN
.B \-\-mime
.I MIME_TYPE
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wayback
is a concurrent, browser-impersonating scraper written in Rust that downloads
archived assets from the Internet Archive's Wayback Machine CDX API without
being blocked by anti-bot measures.
.PP
It uses
.B libcurl-impersonate
to mimic the TLS fingerprint and HTTP headers of real browsers (Chrome, Firefox,
Edge, Safari, and Tor Browser), allowing it to bypass bot-detection mechanisms
that reject standard HTTP clients.
.PP
Results are deduplicated by URL key, keeping the latest captured version of each
asset. Downloads are journalled to a JSON file so interrupted sessions can be
resumed with
.BR \-\-resume .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-url \ \fIDOMAIN\fR
The target domain to scrape (e.g.\&
.IR wokwi.com )
or a full CDX search URL.
This option is \fBrequired\fR.
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-mime \ \fIMIME_TYPE\fR
The MIME type to filter on the CDX API (e.g.\&
.IR application/wasm ,
.IR image/png ,
.IR text/css ).
This option is \fBrequired\fR.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output\-dir \ \fIDIR\fR
Directory where downloaded assets and the session journal will be stored.
Defaults to
.IR downloads/ .
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-browser \ \fIPROFILE\fR
Browser profile to impersonate.
Valid values:
.IR chrome ,
.IR firefox ,
.IR edge ,
.IR safari ,
.IR tor ,
and versioned variants such as
.IR chrome124 ,
.IR firefox135 .
Defaults to
.IR chrome .
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-resume
Resume a previously interrupted download session by loading the journal from
the output directory.
.TP
.B \-\-retry\-errors \ \fIPATTERN\fR
Retry only downloads whose error message contains
.I PATTERN
(case-insensitive substring match).
Use
.B all
to retry every failed download.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-threads \ \fIN\fR
Number of concurrent downloader threads (default:
.BR 4 ).
.TP
.B \-\-max\-retries \ \fIN\fR
Maximum number of retry attempts per individual download (default:
.BR 5 ).
Retries use exponential back-off starting at 500 ms.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging to stdout.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a short help summary.
.BR \-\-help
prints the full help with all defaults.
.SH EXAMPLES
Download all archived WebAssembly files from
.IR wokwi.com :
.PP
.RS
.EX
wayback \-\-url wokwi.com \-\-mime application/wasm
.EE
.RE
.PP
Download archived PNG images using Firefox 135 impersonation with 8 threads:
.PP
.RS
.EX
wayback \-\-url example.com \-\-mime image/png \e
        \-\-browser firefox135 \-\-threads 8 \e
        \-\-output\-dir ./images
.EE
.RE
.PP
Resume an interrupted session and retry all previously failed downloads:
.PP
.RS
.EX
wayback \-\-url example.com \-\-mime text/css \e
        \-\-resume \-\-retry\-errors all
.EE
.RE
.PP
Use a full CDX API URL directly:
.PP
.RS
.EX
wayback \-\-url "http://web.archive.org/cdx/search/cdx?url=example.com/*&filter=mimetype:image/png&collapse=urlkey&output=json" \e
        \-\-mime image/png
.EE
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I <output\-dir>/download_journal.json
Session journal recording the status (Pending, Success, Failed) of every
discovered asset.
Written atomically via a temporary file to prevent corruption.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.B wayback
does not read any environment variables directly, but it relies on
.B libcurl-impersonate
being available in the dynamic linker search path (see
.IR LD_LIBRARY_PATH " or " /etc/ld.so.conf ).
.SH PREREQUISITES
.B wayback
requires
.B libcurl-impersonate
at runtime to perform browser-impersonated TLS handshakes.
This library is not packaged via APT; install it manually:
.PP
.RS
.EX
git clone https://github.com/lwthiker/curl-impersonate
cd curl-impersonate
make install
sudo ldconfig
.EE
.RE
.PP
Full installation instructions are available in the project README at
.UR https://github.com/ajsb85/wayback\-impersonator
.UE .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful completion.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred (bad argument, CDX query failure, runtime error).
.TP
.B 2
Invalid command-line arguments (printed by clap).
